      • calcClampedProbExceed

        @Deprecated
public static double calcClampedProbExceed(double μ,
                                      double σ,
                                      double value,
                                      ExceedanceModel truncType,
                                      double truncLevel,
                                      double clamp)
        Deprecated. 
        Compute the 'clamped' probability of exceeding a value in a normal distribution defined by μ and σ, where clamp is an absolute maximum that may be above or below any μ + n * σ truncation. For two-sided truncation, the lower bound is set to a sigma based value (e.g. μ - n * σ) that may yield an assymmetric trunction.
        Parameters:
        μ - mean
        σ - standard deviation
        value - to exceed
        truncType - none, one-sided, or two-sided truncation
        truncLevel - in number of standard deviations
        clamp - maximum allowable value

        Deprecated. 
        Populates the supplied sequence with probabilites of exceeding its x-values in a normal distribution defined by μ and σ. If clamp is true, the lesser of 3*sigma and clampVal is used to truncate the upper part of the underlying Gaussian.
        Parameters:
        μ - log mean ground motion
        σ - log std deviation of ground motion
        values - to exceed
        truncType - none, one-sided, or two-sided truncation
        truncLevel - in number of standard deviations
        Returns:
